article.description: — Dontarius James had 26 points as Jacksonville ended its seven-game losing streak, getting past Lipscomb 66-60 on Friday night.
article.headline: James scores 26 to lead Jacksonville over Lipscomb 66-60
article.linkText: James scores 26 to lead Jacksonville over Lipscomb 66-60
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Dontarius James had 26 points as Jacksonville ended its seven-game losing streak, getting past Lipscomb 66-60 on Friday night. Tyreese Davis had 15 points for Jacksonville (10-11, 4-7 Atlantic Sun Conference). Bryce Workman added 12 points and nine rebounds. Ahsan Asadullah had 23 points, nine rebounds and three assists for the Bisons (12-10, 6-5). KJ Johnson added 12 points.
